Abbey Miller, left, of Hershey, walks off the green at No. 1 at Lake Maloney Golf Course. (Derek Noehren / The North Platte Telegraph) Posted: Monday, October 12, 2015 9:26 pm Hershey’s Miller enjoying her state tourney experience By Andrew Bottrell abottrell@nptelegraph.com nptelegraph.com 
LAKE MALONEY — Though she goes to school less than 20 miles away, Abby Miller played her first full round at Lake Maloney Golf Course on Friday. 
The second time she shot a 106 in the first round of the Class C State Girls Golf Championship on Monday. The Hershey senior finished the first round tied for 47th with Hally Waters, of Dundy County-Stratton.     Subscription required
